@startuml
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam sequenceArrowColor #333333
skinparam sequenceParticipantBorderColor #333333
skinparam sequenceLifeLineBorderColor #CCCCCC

title Employer View Candidate Profile - Authorization Flow

actor "Employer" as Employer
actor "Candidate" as Candidate
participant "Frontend" as FE
participant "User Router\nGET /users/{user_id}" as UserEndpoint
database "PostgreSQL" as DB

note over Employer, DB
  EMPLOYER VIEWING CANDIDATE PROFILE
  ==================================
  Authorization required:
  - Self: Always allowed
  - Admin: Always allowed
  - Employer: Only if candidate applied to their jobs
end note

== Scenario 1: Employer Views Candidate Who Applied ==

note over Employer, DB
  Employer is viewing candidates who applied to their job posting.
  Frontend will call API to get candidate profile.
end note

Employer ->> FE: Clicks "View Profile" on candidate\n(in job applicants list)
FE ->> UserEndpoint: GET /users/{candidate_id}\n(Authorization: Bearer token)

note over UserEndpoint
  Extract from token:
  - current_user_id
  - current_user_role
end note

== Step 1: Authorization Check ==

UserEndpoint ->> UserEndpoint: can_access_profile(\n  current_user_id,\n  current_user_role,\n  target_user_id\n)

note right
  Authorization Logic:
  1. IF current_user_id == target_user_id → ALLOW (self)
  2. IF current_user_role == "admin" → ALLOW (admin)
  3. IF current_user_role == "employer" → CHECK application
  4. ELSE → DENY
end note

== Step 2: Check Application (for Employer) ==

alt Current user is NOT employer
  UserEndpoint ->> UserEndpoint: Skip application check
else Current user IS employer
end note

UserEndpoint ->> DB: SELECT EXISTS (
  SELECT 1 FROM applications a
  JOIN jobs j ON a.job_id = j.id
  JOIN users_companies uc ON j.company_id = uc.company_id
  WHERE a.candidate_id = ?
  AND uc.user_id = ?
)

note right
  Checks if:
  1. Candidate has ANY application
  2. The job belongs to employer's company
end note

DB -->> UserEndpoint: true/false (has_applied)

alt Not Authorized (no application)
  UserEndpoint -->> FE: HTTP 403 Forbidden\n{"detail": "Not authorized"}
  FE -->> Employer: "You cannot view this profile"
  
  note over Employer
    Employer tried to access candidate who
    hasn't applied to their jobs.
    Authorization blocked!
  end note
  
else Authorized
end note

== Step 3: Get User Profile with CV Data ==

UserEndpoint ->> DB: Query user profile\n+ CV extracted data

note right
  Query includes:
  - Basic info (id, email, full_name, phone)
  - CV extracted fields (flattened):
    - summary
    - skills[]
    - languages[]
    - experience[]
    - education[]
    - certifications[]
end note

DB -->> UserEndpoint: User profile with CV data

== Step 4: Return Profile ==

UserEndpoint -->> FE: User profile response\n(JSON with all fields)
FE -->> Employer: Display candidate profile\nwith full details

note over Employer
  Employer can now see:
  - Candidate contact info
  - Work experience
  - Education background
  - Skills
  - Languages
  - Certifications
end note

== Scenario 2: Random Access Attempt (Blocked) ==

actor "RandomUser" as RandomUser

note over RandomUser, UserEndpoint
  Random user tries to access
  another user's profile directly
end note

RandomUser ->> FE: GET /users/12345\n(Arbitrary user ID)
FE ->> UserEndpoint: GET /users/12345

UserEndpoint ->> UserEndpoint: Check authorization

note right
  RandomUser:
  - Not the target user (id mismatch)
  - Not admin
  - Not employer (or different company)
end note

UserEndpoint -->> FE: HTTP 403 Forbidden\n{"detail": "Not authorized"}
FE -->> RandomUser: "Not authorized"

note over RandomUser
  Access denied!
  Cannot view other users' profiles
  without proper authorization.
end note

== Authorization Rules Summary ==

note over UserEndpoint
  GET /users/{user_id} Authorization Rules:
  ========================================
  
  | Caller Role | Can Access | Condition |
  |-------------|------------|-----------|
  | Self (same user) | ✅ YES | user_id == current_user.id |
  | Admin | ✅ YES | Always |
  | Employer | ✅ YES | Candidate applied to employer's jobs |
  | Other | ❌ NO | Always denied |
  
  Error Response: HTTP 403 "Not authorized"
end note

@enduml
